          <div class="feature-split__content">
            <h2>Newark Castle</h2>
            <p>Standing proudly on the banks of the River Trent, Newark Castle is the town's most iconic landmark. Founded around 1133 by Alexander, Bishop of Lincoln, the castle was rebuilt in red sandstone and developed into one of the finest fortified residences in medieval England.</p>
            <p>The gatehouse, with its elegant Romanesque arches, is considered one of the best-preserved 12th-century gatehouses in the country. Visitors can explore the castle grounds and gardens for free, take guided tours of the towers and underground passages, and enjoy stunning views over the river.</p>
            <p>The castle is a Grade I listed building and scheduled monument, recognised as a structure of international importance.</p>
