            <h2>The Church of St Mary Magdalene</h2>
            <p>Dominating the skyline with its magnificent 252-foot (77m) spire, the Church of St Mary Magdalene is built on the scale of a cathedral. Dating from the 12th century, this Grade I listed church is one of the grandest parish churches in England.</p>
            <p>Among its treasures is a large Flemish brass commemorating Alan Fleming, a wealthy wool merchant who died in 1375. Measuring over 9 feet tall, it is one of the largest of its kind in the country. The church is a testament to the wealth that Newark's medieval wool and cloth trade brought to the town.</p>
