        <div class="grid grid--2">
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>William Ewart Gladstone</h3>
            <p>The four-time Prime Minister was MP for Newark from 1832 to 1845 and made his first public speech at the Clinton Arms on the Market Square. His early political career was shaped in the town.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>King John</h3>
            <p>While not from Newark, King John's death at the castle in 1216 is one of the most significant events in the town's history and in English medieval history.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>Sir Donald Wolfit</h3>
            <p>The acclaimed Shakespearean actor was born in Newark in 1902. He was considered one of the last great actor-managers and was knighted for his services to the theatre.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>Magnus the Magnificent</h3>
            <p>Thomas Magnus, a Tudor diplomat and priest, founded the Magnus Grammar School in Newark in 1530. The school — now The Magnus Church of England Academy — continues his educational legacy today.</p>
